programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.sub-title: Come Dine with Me: Rugby World Cup Special.
programme.desc: Four former rugby union players try to host the best dinner party for a chance of winning the £1,000 prize for their chosen charities. Kyran Bracken kicks off the week with a game of egg Russian roulette, followed by Martin Offiah, who plans a night of fine dining including mussels and a Nigerian stew. Victor Ubogu then takes the reins, introducing his guests to some sheep, before Gareth Chilcott ends the competition by trying to liven up the hung-over diners.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four Olympians compete to win the £1,000 prize for their chosen charities, beginning with former world champion javelin thrower Fatima Whitbread, who prepares a light and healthy meal. Ex-5,000m world record-holder Zola Budd cooks family inspired recipes, former high-jumper Dalton Grant hosts a Caribbean-themed night and Olympic 400m hurdles bronze medallist Kriss Akabusi whips his guests into shape with help from a military drill instructor.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four amateur chefs compete for the £1,000 prize in Luton, Bedfordshire. B&B owner Alison McGaw, fireman Gary Salvage, feisty mother Alex Lipa and fitness trainer Kirkland Hay take turns hosting dinner parties featuring fetish equipment and carefully selected gifts that makes one of the diners cry.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: With their two daughters ready to leave home, adventurous Preston couple Geoff and Sally Taylor are looking to wind down and spend more quality time together. They fell in love with Costa Rica when they visited it on holiday and have decided to buy a holiday home on its Pacific Coast, so Ben Hillman shows the duo five properties in the region within their £300,000 budget.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: Ever since Jacqueline Priddin's parents moved to the Costa del Sol, she and husband Anthony have dreamt of also buying a place there for them and their daughter Izzy. Now they have decided to make that happen, so Ben Hillman shows them five homes in the inland area west of Malaga that suit their £50,000 budget. But will it be a town house or a rustic finca that wins them over?.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun
programme.desc: The Caribbean island of Nevis is very close to Steven and Murila Fifer's hearts. Murila was born there, and the couple have visited the place together many times over the years. They have now decided their dream holiday home should be on the island, so Scarlette Douglas shows them five properties within their £330,000 budget. Will they fall for a country villa or a beach-side home?.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four contestants from Colchester, Essex, battle it out for the £1,000 prize in the dinner party challenge, with Vanessa opening proceedings in what she claims is the most haunted house in the country. Foodie Michael tries to impress with his mobile-phone controlled lamb dish on the next night. Basketball coach Maurice turns on the gastronomic charm with steak and chicken consomme served with a side order of poetry, but retired hairdresser Maureen's evening turns into a nightmare on the final evening.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four contestants in York battle it out, with Svenja starting proceedings in York with her German take on British food, followed by charming waiter Oli, who pins his hopes on quality service and table manners. Night three sees events manager Nichola aiming to bring some sunshine to the table with her holiday-themed menu, and fishery owner Craig concludes the dinner parties with a down-to-earth selection and a spectacular fireworks show.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
programme.desc: Gordon Ramsay visits Mojito, a Cuban cafe in Brooklyn, New York. The restaurant was the shared dream of two newlyweds who have separated since its opening, and whose constant public quarrelling is distracting staff and driving customers away.(n)

programme.title: Roald Dahl's Most Marvellous Book
programme.desc: David Walliams presents a look at the author's 10 most popular children's books to mark the centenary of his birth. Viewers have the chance to vote for their favourite of the 10 novels featured, which include Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, The BFG, The Witches, Matilda and The Twits. Featuring contributions from Steven Spielberg, Julie Walters, Richard Curtis, Mackenzie Crook, Jarvis Cocker, Johnny Vegas, Jessica Hynes and Miriam Margolyes.(n)

programme.title: Speed with Guy Martin
programme.desc: The motorcycle racer competes in the Nevada Open Road Challenge, the fastest road race in the world, in which Highway 318 is closed to allow top of the line supercars to compete in time trials. Guy decides to make the challenge even greater by entering the contest in his Ford Transit van - but unfortunately, a crash has left the vehicle in need of some extensive repair work. He gathers a team of race engineers to rebuild the van and turn it into a racing machine capable of taking on some of the world's fastest cars.(n)

programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: The nation's favourite armchair critics share their opinions on what they have been watching during the week. The programme captures their instant reactions to Flowers, Fierce, Louis Theroux: Drinking to Oblivion, Horizon: How to Find Love Online, Caravanner of the Year and Antiques Roadshow.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts the popular quiz with guest captain Claudia Winkleman and Johnny Vegas going up against Jon Richardson and Reginald D Hunter. Sara Pascoe joins resident lexicographer Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner, while Rachel Riley looks after the numbers and letters.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Benefit Tenants
programme.desc: In Manchester, letting agent Amin is on the trail of a woman who has fallen behind in her rent. However, when he arrives at her house, he discovers a nasty surprise. Meanwhile, a young agent finds himself caught in the middle of one of his landlords and a tenant who owes over £3,600 in rent arrears and is refusing to pay. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Obsessive Compulsive Cleaners

programme.desc: Action from day four of the Games in Rio. programme.desc: Gabby Logan presents coverage of the half-marathon that runs from Newcastle upon Tyne to South Shields, as Mo Farah attempts to retain his title in the men's elite race. The British athlete is in superb form, having recently won gold in the 5,000 and 10,000m races at the Olympic Games in Rio di Janeiro. Those victories completed a historic `double double' for Farah, having won the same races at the London 2012 Olympics. Commentary comes from Steve Cram, Brendan Foster and Paula Radcliffe, with reports by Denise Lewis and Colin Jackson.(n)

programme.desc: Gregg Wallace and Chris Bavin are in Hampshire to help the Haynes family, whose conflicting tastes mean they are eating different meals, which is causing waste and their food bills to spiral. Child minder Jodie has other mouths to feed in the evening, as well as her two young children, while father Rob is often home late and prefers spicier food, so buys pre-prepared meals for himself. However, their disparaging tastes mean the family is going to the shops 11 times a week and spending over twice the national average.(n)

Hugh discovers how the capuchin monkeys of Costa Rica have such a fantastic team spirit, biologist Patrick Aryee investigates man's relationship with the vulture - nature's most infamous scavenger - and zoologist Lucy Cooke finds out about the medicine in Kentucky that may improve a rare pig's relationship problems. Conservationist Giles Clark ventures into the rainforests of Thailand to find out how a clever matchmaking technique could help save the clouded leopard from extinction.(n)

Contestants create a wide range of sweets and pastry dishes, including cakes, pies, and patisserie, before judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood cast a critical eye over their efforts. Presented by Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins.(n)

programme.title: Lifeline

programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman present as another selection of celebrities take part in the general knowledge quiz. This time, the duo open the contest to famous faces who made a name for themselves early in life. Outnumbered's Tyger Drew-Honey teams up with This Is England's Thomas Turgoose, while Willy Wonka & the Chocolate Factory's Julie Dawn Cole joins forces with Oliver! star Mark Lester. Plus, former Grange Hill stars Lee MacDonald and Erkan Mustafa take on former classmate Michelle Gayle as she partners ex-Coronation Street actor Adam Rickitt.(n)

One visitor to the show has a fascination with design diagrams inspired by an earlier episode - and brings in a collection of 650.(n)

programme.title: Poldark
programme.desc: The election results are announced, with Unwin tied for the second seat - but the announcement provokes public fury and he is attacked by an angry mob. Demelza tries to influence the outcome of Ross's trial by appealing directly to Justice Lister, but is stopped by an eavesdropping George. Dwight tries to persuade Francis not to kill himself, and Jud gives a surprising testimony. Clymer gives Ross a speech to make at the conclusion of his trial - but he rejects it, choosing to stick to his principles.(n)

Thriller based on the 1985 BBC series, starring Mel Gibson, Ray Winstone, Danny Huston, Bojana Novakovic, Shawn Roberts and David Aaron Baker.(n)

Presented by Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman.(n)

programme.desc: Denise locks herself away and tries to distract herself from dealing with her pregnancy, despite Carmel's attempts to help. Sonia is frustrated when she is left to care for Sylvie yet again, so Dot encourages her to put herself and Bex first for once. Jane and Ian continue to drift apart when he refuses to talk to her, Lee questions whether he will be a good father and Carmel pulls Buster up for breaking the rules on the market.(n)

programme.title: Panorama
programme.sub-title: Why Are Gambling Machines Addictive? - Panorama.
programme.desc: Wendy Bendel embarks on a highly personal journey to investigate the dangers posed by fixed-odds betting terminals, found in many bookmakers across the UK. Wendy's partner killed himself after struggling with a 20-year gambling addiction, and in a confessional note, he singled out the high-stakes, high-frequency devices as a key obstacle he longed to overcome, in what would eventually prove to be a losing battle. Wendy sets out to determine what it is about these betting machines that makes them so addictive, and discovers evidence that suggests they are capable of affecting the brains of long-term gamblers. The billions these terminals are able to generate have divided the gambling industry, and Wendy hears from some former insiders who are now accusing bookies of prioritising profits over the health and wellbeing of their clients.(n)

programme.title: Crimewatch

Members of the public have been invited to vote for their favourite projects across seven categories; Arts, Education, Environment, Heritage, Health, Sport and Voluntary/Charity, and the winners in each field will take home a £3,000 cash prize for their cause. The Wanted's Nathan Sykes is on hand to provide musical entertainment, and Barrowman also pays tribute to the achievements of Team GB's Olympic heroes. The ceremony concludes with the presentation of the Special Achievement Award.(n)

programme.desc: The South West competitors Chris Wheeler, Jude Kereama and Josh Eggleton prepare main courses as they compete to be crowned champion. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: South West chefs Jude Kereama, Josh Eggleton and Chris Wheeler continue the battle to cook at a banquet held at the Palace of Westminster celebrating ordinary Britons honoured by the Queen. As each of them prepare their desserts, they will all be out to impress as only two can make it through to tomorrow's regional final.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two remaining South West chefs cook their entire menus again for judges Prue Leith, Oliver Peyton and Matthew Fort. The arbitrators are joined by journalist and restaurant critic Grace Dent, who helps them decide which budding chef will go forward to the national finals.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Anita Manning and Adam Patridge search for collectibles at Crathes Castle in Aberdeenshire, but it is Paul Martin who seems to scoop a big prize when he spots a valuable 19th-century oriental armrest. The presenter also learns about the area's shipbuilding past.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Photographer Vianet Djenguet travels to The Republic of Congo, the country he was born in, to document the incredible environments and wildlife. His journey stretches from the coastline to rainforests untouched by human development, and includes encounters with animals including chimpanzees, forest elephants and lowland gorillas.(n)

programme.title: The Story of Are You Being Served
programme.desc: The cast, crew and writers of the much-loved TV classic about a department store look back on its 13-year run. At its peak, the sitcom - inspired by writer Jeremy Lloyd's time working at former London store Simpsons - attracted up to 22 million viewers. Alexander Armstrong narrates.(n)

programme.title: Athletics
programme.desc: Ore Oduba presents action from the half-marathon that ran from Newcastle upon Tyne to South Shields, as Mo Farah attempted to retain his title in the men's elite race.(n)

programme.title: New York: America's Busiest City
programme.desc: Anita Rani, Ade Adepitan, Ant Anstead and Dan Snow look at food consumption in the Big Apple. From dusk until dawn at the New Fulton fish market in The Bronx, they uncover the hidden night time operations, hard-nosed negotiations and price fluctuations of this enormous wholesale operation. Ade also looks into local apple production, Anita visits a cattle farm that supplies the region's steakhouses, Ant visits the New NY Bridge, and Dan heads to Freshkills on Staten Island. Once the world's biggest landfill, it's been transformed into 2,200 acres of parkland.(n)

programme.title: Scotland and the Battle for Britain
programme.desc: Andrew Marr presents a two-part programme exploring the transformation of Scottish politics in recent years. The first programme looks back over the shift in power that has occurred since the 1950s, with the Unionists losing ground to Labour, who have ultimately given way to the SNP. With contributions from leading political figures including Nicola Sturgeon, Alex Salmond and Tony Blair.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Jimmy Carr and the Science of Laughter - A Horizon Special.
programme.desc: The comedian takes over the science programme in a special episode for BBC's sitcom season, turning it into a chat show with eminent scientists as guests. He talks to them about the nature of laughter, with the studio audiences serving as guinea pigs in his attempt to get to the bottom of what laughter is, what it has to do with comedy, and why human beings find it a pleasurable sensation. The programme reveals that laughter predates the human species and may have played a vital role in our evolution.(n)

programme.title: Fleabag
programme.desc: Claire takes Fleabag to an all-female silent retreat. What should be a period of peaceful solitude is disrupted by some explosive secrets coming to light, a surprising connection with an old acquaintance, and an unusual neighbouring workshop. Comedy, written by and starring Phoebe Waller-Bridge.(n)

programme.title: Murder in Successville
programme.desc: George Shelley helps Sleet solve the murder of computer hacker Ed Sheeran. Forensics officer Angela Merkel is convinced that he was killed for breaking into the personal files of some very powerful people, and a banker, an arms dealer and a technology entrepreneur are likely suspects - but Sleet is more concerned that the case does not get in the way of his own plans to launch a new app.(n)

programme.title: Absolutely Fashion: Inside British Vogue
programme.desc: For the first time in British Vogue's 100-year history, TV cameras have been allowed to film behind closed doors, granting documentary maker Richard Macer unprecedented access to the UK's style bible, its cover stars, designers, and those who run it, as the magazine prepares to celebrate its centenary. In the first of two programmes, editor-in-chief Alexandra Shulman decides she wants to change the magazine's front covers to appeal to a younger audience - the Instagram generation. Will this new relaxed style work for British Vogue?.(n)

programme.title: Point Blank
programme.desc: A nurse saves the life of a dangerous criminal, whom the police keep under armed guard at the hospital where he works. The nurse receives a chilling message from his patient's henchmen, who have kidnapped his wife and will kill her unless he helps their boss escape. Action thriller, starring Gilles Lellouche and Roschdy Zem. In French.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Reports on harvest time around the UK. Anita Rani picks peppermint to make cocktails, while Matt Baker discovers how harvesting has changed over the years at the Gaddesden Estate, and John Craven gathers cobnuts. Plus, Joe Crowley investigates how many of the farm brands on sale in supermarkets actually come from a farm, and Adam Henson celebrates 40 years of One Man and His Dog.(n)

programme.desc: Sacha's birthday celebrations do not go according to plan, while Mo's delight at Mr T's return is short-lived. Serena tries to cover her confused feelings for Bernie.(n)

programme.sub-title: Kate Humble: My Sheepdog and Me.
programme.desc: The broadcaster sets out to breed Welsh sheepdog puppies from her beloved pet Teg, learns about the threat facing British herding dogs and tries to train Teg to work in the traditional Welsh way. Along the way, Kate meets a team at the University of Aberystwyth whose groundbreaking DNA research reveals some remarkable facts about the breed, and if Teg can produce a litter of healthy puppies, it would play a big part in helping one of Britain's unique herding dogs survive for generations to come.(n)

programme.desc: Giles decides upon an extreme course of action to win back Daphne, while Angie jets off to the Seychelles on a modelling assignment.(n)

programme.desc: Joe Maplin hatches a hare-brained scheme to stop a hospital being built next to the camp site, ordering staff to make a din from dawn till dusk while the council committee conduct an inspection visit. Jimmy Perry and David Croft's comedy, starring Ruth Madoc, Paul Shane and Su Pollard.(n)

programme.title: Yes Minister
programme.desc: Hacker and Sir Humphrey are summoned to appear before a select committee investigating charges of waste in the ministry, where they frantically pass the buck to protect themselves and each other. Starring Paul Eddington and Nigel Hawthorne.(n)

programme.title: The Great Interior Design Challenge
programme.sub-title: Great Interior Design Challenge: Ultimate Secrets.
programme.desc: The final programme brings together the ultimate rules of design, room by room, featuring insider techniques for a better home used by regular judges Sophie Robinson and Daniel Hopwood as well as contributors Oliver Heath, Orla Kiely and Kelly Hoppen. Presenter and architectural historian Tom Dyckhoff gives his own historic tour of the house - explaining how homes have shaped up over the years.(n)

programme.title: The Great Rift: Africa's Wild Heart
programme.desc: How geological forces created the Great Rift Valley in East Africa, and why a string of volcanos running from Ethiopia to Tanzania provides the ideal habitat for some of the world's most extraordinary wildlife. The programme also discovers many newly discovered species have made their homes among the dangerous peaks, where they have developed unorthodox methods of coping with the challenging terrain.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Antiques experts Anita Manning and Will Axon head to Wells Cathedral in Somerset to uncover some hidden treasures to be sold at auction. Items include a pair of paintings by an amateur artist and a collection of shot and powder flasks. Plus, Paul Martin takes a journey around the historic centre of the ancient city.(n)

programme.title: Debatable
programme.desc: Patrick Kielty hosts the quiz show as actor Nigel Havers, broadcaster Konnie Huq and actor Christopher Biggins try to help Jim from Aberdeen to the cash prize.(n)

programme.title: Make Me an Egghead
programme.desc: Jeremy Vine hosts a search for the nation's best quizzing brains, with the two series winners gaining the ultimate prize of places on the panel of resident experts on Eggheads.(n)

programme.title: Garden Rescue
programme.desc: Charlie Dimmock and Dave and Harry Rich are in Hereford, where they come up with ideas to transform a back garden for a family that has four generations living in the same house. With a limited budget, the designers come up with some ideas for creating garden sculptures and focal points on a shoestring. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the North West region heats sees returning contender Matt Worswick and newcomers Adam Reid and Kim Woodward prepare their starters for the banquet being held at the Palace of Westminster, in celebration of everyday Great Britons honoured by the Queen. The flavour combinations include luxurious king crab, classic liver and bacon and a selection of Indian and East African delicacies.(n)

programme.title: University Challenge
programme.desc: In the 10th of the academic quiz's first-round matches, four students from the University of Edinburgh pit their wits against a team from the University of Durham in a bid to reach the second stage of the competition. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions.(n)

programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell welcomes three wrestling fans and a trio from Clare College, Cambridge to the quiz testing general knowledge and lateral thinking. The teams must make connections between groups of four things that may appear at first not to be linked, with one set of clues consisting of single-fingered rock-climbing hold, Spanish monkey, North American glandular fever and single-channel sound reproduction.(n)

programme.title: Ripper Street
programme.desc: Jackson feels the pressure as a murder has links to a man who aided Long Susan's escape from Newgate, and he needs to solve the case without the truth about Susan emerging. One month has passed since Inspector Reid returned to H Division and he and Drake are once more in harmony, while Susan works to carve a place for herself at the docks, revealing more of her dark past to her villainous guardian Abel Croker.(n)

programme.title: Live at the Apollo
programme.desc: Romesh Ranganathan comperes an evening of stand-up at London's Hammersmith Apollo, treating the audience to his own brand of humour before introducing routines by comedy circuit stars Jason Byrne and Stewart Francis.(n)

programme.title: Newsnight
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events, presented by Kirsty Wark.(n)

programme.title: Trust Me, I'm a Doctor
programme.desc: Dr Saleyha Ahsan investigates the signs and symptoms of depression, asking what people should look out for, Michael Mosley reveals a new discovery that could help improve people's eyesight, and Dr Chris van Tulleken carries out an experiment with the University of Worcester to find out the pros and cons of going gluten-free. Surgeon Gabriel Weston witnesses a breakthrough that could cure rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune diseases.(n)

programme.title: From Andy Pandy to Zebedee: The Golden Age of Children's TV
programme.desc: The story of the struggle to deliver television programmes for children, who were an often overlooked audience in the days before everything went digital. Includes interviews with pioneers of children's TV, such as Bernard Cribbins, Derek Griffiths, Janet Ellis, Johnny Ball and John Craven. Narrated by Nigel Planer.(n)

programme.title: Madness on Wheels: Rallying's Craziest Years
programme.desc: The evolution of the motorsport in the 1980s, which saw the relaxation of rules and the emergence of the Group B era. Hugely powerful vehicles including the Peugeot 205 T16, Ford RS200, Lancia Delta S4, Audi Quattro S1 and MG Metro 6R4 reached higher speeds than ever before, creating a surge in the sport's popularity - but also posing an enormous risk to spectators. With contributions by former world champions Ari Vatanen, Walter Roehrl and Stig Blomqvist, plus driver Michele Mouton, ex-Lancia team manager Cesare Fiorio and current FIA president Jean Todt.(n)

programme.title: The Comet's Tale
programme.desc: The story of man's understanding of comets, once thought to signal impending doom, revealing how space missions have provided important information on what they are made of, where they come from, and how they can influence events on Earth.(n)

programme.title: The Sky at Night
programme.sub-title: Interstellar: The Journey to Proxima B.
programme.desc: Chris Lintott and Maggie Aderin-Pocock report on the recent discovery of a planet with similar qualities to Earth orbiting Proxima Centauri, the nearest star to our solar system. The programme examines what the environment of this world might be like and the logistics of building a spacecraft capable of travelling 4.23 light years to reach it.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Horizon: How Big Is the Universe?.
programme.desc: Cosmologists discuss their project to create a map of everything in existence, and reveal that their research has yielded some highly unexpected results, creating a picture stranger than anything they had imagined. Scientists also explain why the map suggests the universe may not be an all-encompassing entity - but merely the starting point for something much bigger.(n)

programme.title: Metamorphosis - The Science of Change
programme.desc: David Malone explores the processes involved in metamorphosis, the means through which one being transforms into another, and investigates why this distinctive change seems to have such a powerful grasp on the human imagination. Along the way, he highlights examples throughout the scope of historical fiction, from the epics of Ovid to the surreal short stories of Franz Kafka and the fantasy heroics of Marvel's X-Men.(n)

programme.title: Operation Crossbow
programme.desc: The little-known story of Spitfire pilots and Allied technicians whose work helped to thwart the Nazis during the Second World War. The programme reveals how stereoscopic 3D photographs were used to help interpreters map every contour of the enemy's territory, and uses personal testimony, computer-generated imagery and original wartime pictures to detail how the initiative was able to uncover some of Hitler's most dangerous secrets. Narrated by Samantha Bond.(n)

programme.title: The Beginning and End of the Universe
programme.desc: Professor Jim Al-Khalili attempts to discover how the universe will end, with a bang or a whimper? He also encounters a mysterious and enigmatic force that promises to change physics for ever.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Horizon: How Big Is the Universe?.

programme.desc: Writer Tom Cunliffe turns his attention to the Reaper, the biggest sailing lugger ever to fish the seas at 70ft long, and capable of pulling in 10 tons of herring in a single haul. He learns about the origins and history of the vessel, which played an important role in supplying food to Britain after the Second World War.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: The importance of power in the animal kingdom, revealing how dominant creatures have the best access to food and water, and are also the most attractive to the opposite sex. An orphaned young chimp tries to climb the social ladder, but his troop is ruled by big, aggressive males and his first attempt to join them ends in a beating. A meerkat society will only allow newcomers in if they know how to deal with a venomous snake. And the only way to occupy the top spot in a meadow of kangaroos is to beat the ruling male in a boxing match - but few have challenged the current incumbent, who stands at 8ft. Will any animal dare take him on? David Attenborough narrates.(n)

programme.title: British Sitcom: 60 Years of Laughing at Ourselves
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the history of the British TV sitcom, from Hancock's Half Hour in the 1950s to the present day, revealing the inspiration behind some of the most enduring characters and how comedy has reflected changing attitudes in society. Narrated by Rebecca Front, and featuring contributions from writers and actors including Steve Coogan, Richard Curtis, James Corden, Graham Linehan, Dick Clement and Ian La Frenais.(n)

programme.title: Timeshift
programme.sub-title: Full Throttle: The Glory Days of British Motorbikes.
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the history and culture of motorcycling in Britain - from army officer TE Lawrence's passion for the vehicles in the 1920s, to the key role they played in the Second World War, and the perceived `golden age' of the 1950s - when the lifestyle associated with motorcyclists began to attract social disapproval and conflict. Narrated by John Hannah.(n)

programme.title: The Genius of Turner: Painting the Industrial Revolution
programme.desc: Docu-drama revealing there is more to painter JMW Turner than his famous landscapes, examining key paintings incorporating machines, science and technology that reflect the scientific and industrial revolutions he lived through. Including interviews with historian Simon Schama and artist Tracey Emin. Narrated by Samuel West, with Thomas Coombes portraying Turner.(n)

Comedy, based on the 1960s TV series, with Steve Carell, Anne Hathaway, Dwayne Johnson, Alan Arkin, Terence Stamp and James Caan.(n)

Controversial comedy, starring James Franco, Seth Rogen and Lizzy Caplan.(n)

Comedy sequel, starring Mike Myers in multiple roles alongside Heather Graham, Rob Lowe, Robert Wagner, Michael York, Seth Green and Verne Troyer.(n)

Comedy drama, starring Bill Murray, Jaeden Lieberher, Melissa McCarthy and Naomi Watts.(n)

Disney animated fairytale, with the voices of Ilene Woods, William Phipps and Verna Felton.(n)

With the voices of Jennifer Hale and Christopher Daniel Barnes.(n)

Sci-fi thriller, with Sylvester Stallone, Wesley Snipes, Sandra Bullock and Nigel Hawthorne.(n)

Action sequel, directed by and starring Sylvester Stallone. With Julie Benz and Graham McTavish.(n)

Crime drama, starring Brenton Thwaites, Ewan McGregor and Alicia Vikander.(n)

programme.desc: A couple are plagued by the disappearance of their young daughter, eight years after she went missing, and a series of disturbing incidents seem to indicate that she is still alive. Thriller, starring Ryan Reynolds, Kevin Durand, Mireille Enos and Rosario Dawson.(n)

programme.title: Zodiac
programme.desc: Fact-based crime thriller about the tortuous hunt for a mysterious serial killer who terrorised San Francisco in the late 1960s and early 1970s, and taunted the police and media with cryptic messages. Starring Jake Gyllenhaal, Robert Downey Jr, Mark Ruffalo and Brian Cox.(n)

Thriller based on Castle Freeman Jr's novel, starring Julia Stiles, Anthony Hopkins, Alexander Ludwig and Ray Liotta.(n)

Crime drama based on Caryl Ferey's novel, with Forest Whitaker and Orlando Bloom.(n)

programme.title: The Calling

Crime thriller based on Inger Ash Wolfe's novel, starring Susan Sarandon and Donald Sutherland.(n)

programme.title: Angel Flight Down
